    <item>
      <title>Google to ban payday loan advertisements</title>
      <link>http://www.smh.com.au/business/banking-and-finance/google-to-ban-payday-loan-advertisements-20160512-got8ac.html</link>
      <description>The search site will ban all payday loan ads from its site amid concerns the lending practice exploits the poor and vulnerable via loans with sky-high interest rates.</description>
      <pubDate>Thu, 12 May 2016 02:42:12 GMT</pubDate>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">got8ac</guid>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>How Turnbull found riches in Siberia</title>
      <link>http://www.smh.com.au/business/how-turnbull-found-riches-in-siberia-20160512-got530.html</link>
      <description><p><img src="http://images.smh.com.au/2016/05/12/7413477/Thumbnail1009129212gosu35image.related.thumbnail.320x214.got530.png1463066854207.jpg-90x60.jpg" width="90" height="60" style="float:left;margin:4px;border:0px"/></p>It was classic Malcolm Turnbull, during his raging years around the sharemarket, when he made a motza cutting in and out of situations, often in the shifting sands of the media landscape, and then as a mining promoter, an old standby for many of the country's money men over the years.</description>
      <pubDate>Thu, 12 May 2016 15:28:03 GMT</pubDate>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">got530</guid>
    </item>
